[1]
Date: Fri, 29 Jul 2005
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source:The Associated Press, 29 Jul 2005 [edited]
<http://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2005/07/29/AR2005072900734.html>

Dangerous Bird Flu Strain Found in Russia
-----------------------------------------
Investigators have determined that a strain of bird flu virus infecting
fowl in Russia is the type that can infect humans, the Agriculture Ministry
said Friday [29 Jul 2005].
The virus caused the deaths of hundreds of birds in a section of Siberia
this month, but no human infections have been reported.
In a brief statement, the ministry identified the virus as avian flu type A
H5 N1.
"That raises the need for undertaking quarantine measures of the widest
scope," the statement said. Ministry officials could not immediately be
reached for elaboration.
Strains of bird flu have been hitting flocks throughout Asia and some fatal
human cases have been reported there.
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
[According to the current AP media item, the agent is Influenza virus type
A, serotype H5N1. This contradicts earlier media-derived information (see
20050723.2127), according to which the agent was H5N2. An early official
notification on the determined neuraminidase (N) type is urgently required.
- Mod.AS]
